                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.08172/2604.08172v1/figures/pal_teaser.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:An Illustration of our work. (a) We identified that there exist inconsistent global photometric shift across the paired training datasets. (b) As the photometric shift dominates the gradient, learning texture and structure content from the training data becomes difficult. Our PAL helps rebalance the gradient. (c) Equipped with our PAL, the performance gained across 6 tasks, 16 methods, and 16 datasets, with an average gain in PSNR of 0.45dB across 6 tasks.",
                "position": 263
            }
        ]
